'''恭請聖訓'''（{{lang-en|Humble address}}）是指[[英國國會|英國國會]]其中一項[[議事程序|議事程序]]，讓[[英国下议院|下議院]]或[[英國上議院|上議院]]向[[英國君主政體|君主]]進言。例如，當[[御座致辭|御座致辭]]標誌國會新會期開始後，上下兩院會分別動議恭請聖訓，辯論致辭內容和感謝女皇撥冗演說<ref>例子眾多，包括{{cite hansard|house=[[英國下議院|下議院]]|title=Debate on the Address|date=2017-06-22|volume=626|column=228|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2017-06-22/debates/83DB2A19-E587-4268-A161-94A6C2F156F9/DebateOnTheAddress}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2017-06-22/debates/83DB2A19-E587-4268-A161-94A6C2F156F9/DebateOnTheAddress |date=20181128210636 }}</ref>。

== 提供文件 ==
'''恭請聖訓提供文件'''（{{Lang|en|Humble address for a return}}）讓國會下議院或上議院任一院請求女皇陛下及因而[[英國政府|女皇陛下政府]]交出所需文件<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/01/labour-use-arcane-19th-century-parliamentary-procedure-try-force/|title=Labour to use arcane 19th-Century parliamentary procedure to try to force Government to publish secret Brexit files|last=Maidment|first=Jack|date=2017-11-01|work=[[每日電訊報|每日電訊報]]|access-date=2017-11-02|issn=0307-1235|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109043210/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/01/labour-use-arcane-19th-century-parliamentary-procedure-try-force/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|Erskine May: Parliamentary Practice|議會慣例}}》指出，此程序在十九世紀中葉前經常動用，但此後被[[敕書|敕書]]或[[英國國會法令|國會法令]]附帶的解說文件所取代，因而鮮有引用<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://constitution-unit.com/2017/11/10/labours-motion-for-a-return-what-and-why/|title=Labour's 'motion for a return': what and why?|date=2017-11-10|work=The Constitution Unit Blog|access-date=2018-05-02|archive-date=2020-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124034320/https://constitution-unit.com/2017/11/10/labours-motion-for-a-return-what-and-why/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。鑑於恭請聖訓是直接進言英皇，因而具約束力<ref>{{Cite web|title=What is the humble address and why has it forced Brexit files release?|url=https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/4823973/humble-address-labour-brexit-study-conservatives/|accessdate=2020-10-29|date=2017-11-02|work=[[太陽報_(英國)|太陽報]]|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111224701/https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/4823973/humble-address-labour-brexit-study-conservatives/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===2017年===
2017年11月1日，工黨的影子脫歐事務大臣[[施紀賢|施紀賢]]爵士在下議院動議恭請聖訓<ref>{{cite hansard|house=[[英國下議院|下議院]]|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2017-11-01/debates/62139AE8-AA75-42F7-85D3-BB50087ACEFB/ExitingTheEUSectoralImpactAssessments#contribution-C4CBBF0E-BAA0-42A3-8BB6-0D644792327B|column=878|title=Exiting the EU: Sectoral Impact Assessments|volume=630|date=2017-11-01}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2017-11-01/debates/62139AE8-AA75-42F7-85D3-BB50087ACEFB/ExitingTheEUSectoralImpactAssessments#contribution-C4CBBF0E-BAA0-42A3-8BB6-0D644792327B |date=20210124163126 }}</ref>，要求政府公開有關[[英國脫歐|脫歐]]對英國經濟潛在影響的文件<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/nov/01/government-may-bow-to-pressure-to-release-brexit-impact-studies|title=Government may bow to pressure to release Brexit impact studies|first=Peter|last=Walker|date=2017-11-01|work=[[衛報|衛報]]|access-date=2017-11-02|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2020-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201031065138/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/nov/01/government-may-bow-to-pressure-to-release-brexit-impact-studies|dead-url=no}}</ref>；最終在無人反對下獲下議院通過<ref name=":1" />。《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》報導，女皇對於捲入政治事件感到不快，因為君主按{{tsl|en|Constitutional conventions of the United Kingdom|英國憲制慣例|慣例}}要避免干政<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/01/exclusive-queen-not-happy-dragged-labour-row-brexit-papers/|title=Exclusive: Queen 'not happy' after being dragged by Labour into row over Brexit papers|last=Hope|first=Christopher|date=2017-11-01|work=[[每日電訊報|每日電訊報]]|access-date=2018-05-02|issn=0307-1235|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126035649/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/01/exclusive-queen-not-happy-dragged-labour-row-brexit-papers/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。恭請聖訓動議議案如下<ref name=":1">{{cite hansard|house=[[英國下議院|下議院]]|title=Exiting the EU: Sectoral Impact Assessments|volume=630|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2017-11-01/debates/62139AE8-AA75-42F7-85D3-BB50087ACEFB/ExitingTheEUSectoralImpactAssessments#contribution-E8853E96-A83A-4FB6-9F5D-E6703FD00A14|column=931|date=2017-11-01}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2017-11-01/debates/62139AE8-AA75-42F7-85D3-BB50087ACEFB/ExitingTheEUSectoralImpactAssessments#contribution-E8853E96-A83A-4FB6-9F5D-E6703FD00A14 |date=20210124163126 }}</ref>：

{{Quote|恭請女皇陛下聖訓，慷慨並樂意就提交本院2017年6月26日第239題的回答中女皇陛下臣子指示下的各行業分析，以及提交{{tsl|en|Exiting the European Union Select Committee|脫離歐洲聯盟專責委員會}}上述分析引致的影響評估<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8128|title=BRIEFING PAPER Number 8128, Exiting the EU: sectoral impact assessments|last=Maer|first=Lucinda|date=2017-11-01|publisher=下議院圖書館|access-date=2020-10-29|archive-date=2019-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810175929/https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8128|dead-url=no}}</ref>，給予指引。}}

===2018年===
2018年11月13日，工黨的影子脫歐事務大臣[[施紀賢|施紀賢]]爵士在下議院動議恭請聖訓，要求政府公開[[英格蘭及威爾斯檢察總長|律政司]]就英國脫歐協議草擬文本提供的法律意見<ref>{{cite hansard|house=[[英國下議院|下議院]]|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-11-13/debates/EAB2366C-89EA-424B-9B95-B8A9885FEC04/EUWithdrawalAgreementLegalAdvice#contribution-EA44D4EE-46AE-4857-AEE8-927BED854F75|title=EU Withdrawal Agreement: Legal Advice|volume=649|column=189|date=2018-11-13}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-11-13/debates/EAB2366C-89EA-424B-9B95-B8A9885FEC04/EUWithdrawalAgreementLegalAdvice#contribution-EA44D4EE-46AE-4857-AEE8-927BED854F75 |date=20210121061438 }}</ref>；最終在無人反對下獲下議院通過<ref name=":2" />。12月3日，律政司[[喬弗利·科克斯|喬弗利·科克斯]]按決議公佈法律意見，但被議員認為並非完整。因此，國會翌日表決裁定[[英國政府|英國政府]]{{tsl|en|Contempt of Parliament|藐視國會}}，是史上首次<ref>{{cite news|title=Full Brexit legal advice to be published after government loses vote|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/dec/04/mps-demand-for-brexit-legal-advice-too-vague-says-geoffrey-cox|accessdate=2018-12-05|publisher=[[衛報|衛報]]|date=2018-12-04|archive-date=2021-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210314162723/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/dec/04/mps-demand-for-brexit-legal-advice-too-vague-says-geoffrey-cox|dead-url=no}}</ref>。恭請聖訓動議議案如下<ref name=":2">{{cite hansard|house=[[英國下議院|下議院]]|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-11-13/debates/EAB2366C-89EA-424B-9B95-B8A9885FEC04/EUWithdrawalAgreementLegalAdvice#contribution-20D806E0-A5E1-477A-A49F-C1F169C34790|title=EU Withdrawal Agreement: Legal Advice|volume=649|column=235|date=2018-11-13}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-11-13/debates/EAB2366C-89EA-424B-9B95-B8A9885FEC04/EUWithdrawalAgreementLegalAdvice#contribution-20D806E0-A5E1-477A-A49F-C1F169C34790 |date=20210121061438 }}</ref>：

{{quote|恭請女皇聖訓，慷慨並樂意就提交國會以下文件給予指引：任何有關聯合王國離開歐洲聯盟協議草擬文本──包括{{tsl|en|Northern Ireland backstop|北愛爾蘭邊境保障方案}}及聯合王國與歐洲聯盟的未來關係框架──的法律意見全文，包括律政司所提供的<ref>{{cite news |title=Labour aims to force ministers to publish official legal advice on proposed EU deal |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-live-latest-update-theresa-may-deal-legal-advice-irish-border-parliament-a8631091.html |accessdate=2018-11-13 |publisher=[[獨立報|獨立報]] |date=2018-11-13 |archive-date=2020-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109054157/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-live-latest-update-theresa-may-deal-legal-advice-irish-border-parliament-a8631091.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。}}

